title: Measurement and calculation of radioactivities of spallation products by high-energy heavy ions

x4freetext: Measurement and calculation of radioactivities of
spallation products by high-energy heavy ions

x4codes.hlp: RIKEN (Inst. of Physical and Chemical Research), Wako, Japan
Nat.Inst. for Quantum & Radiol.Sci.& Tech., Chiba, Japan

x4freetext: Front sample cross sections as well as excitation
Main reference. See also TITLE and AUTHOR.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.66, p.044607 (2002)
Jour: Jour. of Nuclear Science and Technology Suppl., Vol.2, p.1179 (2002)
Conf: 11th Inter.Symp.on Reactor Dosimetry, Brussels, 2002, p.597 (2002)

x4freetext: - Chemical-form of target is element. Chemical
Samples put on the front of surface were used
for measurements of the reaction cross section
and the mass-yield distributions or produced
nuclides, while samples inserted between the Cu
plates were used for measurements of the
spatial distribution of the residual activities
of produced nuclides in copper and of the
energy dependence of the cross section.

x4codes.hlp: Nat.Inst. for Quantum & Radiol.Sci.& Tech., Chiba, Japan

x4freetext: To measure gamma-ray spectra from samples
To monitor beam current during irradiation
